<item>
            <title>[HBASE-14471] Thrift -  HTTP Error 413 full HEAD if using kerberos authentication</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-14471</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When trying to access a Thrift sever that is kerberized, a HTTP 413 full HEAD error is received. In that case, tcpdump shows http header size exceeded 4k.&lt;br/&gt;
This seems related to the issue outlined in  @&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8816&quot; title=&quot;HTTP Error 413 full HEAD if using kerberos authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-8816&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-8816&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The default header size limit is 4k, follow the fix for @&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-8816&quot; title=&quot;HTTP Error 413 full HEAD if using kerberos authentication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-8816&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-8816&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, propose to increase the header size limit to 64k.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
